<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,762,1976]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,480,1014,1041]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
Description. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[351,473,1014,1041]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Both sexes</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Head rounded trapezoidal (
<figureCitation box="[787,870,1014,1040]" captionStart="FIGURES 38–42" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[186,1380,189,1897]" captionTargetId="figure-17@19.[186,1402,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 38–42. Indoceoplanetes (Indoceoplanetes) fodincana new species ex Coracina papuensis oriomo. 38, male head, dorsal and ventral views. 39, male genitalia, dorsal view. 40, male mesosome, ventral view. 41, male paramere, dorsal view. 42, female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825573" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825573/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Fig. 38</figureCitation>
), lateral margins of preantennal head convex, frons straight to slightly concave. Marginal carina broad, narrowing anterior to 
<emphasis box="[993,1049,1050,1076]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">dsms</emphasis>
, deeply displaced and widened at osculum. Ventral anterior plate rounded, with concave anterior margin and sinuous lateral margins. Head chaetotaxy as in 
<figureCitation box="[212,295,1122,1148]" captionStart="FIGURES 38–42" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[186,1380,189,1897]" captionTargetId="figure-17@19.[186,1402,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 38–42. Indoceoplanetes (Indoceoplanetes) fodincana new species ex Coracina papuensis oriomo. 38, male head, dorsal and ventral views. 39, male genitalia, dorsal view. 40, male mesosome, ventral view. 41, male paramere, dorsal view. 42, female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825573" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825573/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Fig. 38</figureCitation>
. Preantennal nodi wide, bulging. Pre- and post-ocular nodi large, connected dorsally by broad ocular band. Marginal temporal carina slender. Gular plate triangular, lateral margins concave. Thoracic and abdominal segments as in 
<figureCitation box="[328,459,1194,1220]" captionStart="FIGURES 36–37" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[248,1336,200,1917]" captionTargetId="figure-23@18.[232,1356,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 36–37. Indoceoplanetes (Indoceoplanetes) fodincana new species ex Coracina papuensis oriomo. 36, male habitus, dorsal and ventral views. 37, female habitus, dorsal and ventral views." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825571" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825571/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Figs 36–37</figureCitation>
. Base pigmentation pale yellow translucent; head nodi, proepimera, and metepisterna dark brown; marginal and anterior section of marginal temporal carinae, margins of antennal sockets, gular plate, sternal plates IV–VI, and subgenital plates medium brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,762,1976]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,265,1302,1329]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Male.</emphasis>
Thoracic and abdominal chaetotaxy as in 
<figureCitation box="[735,816,1302,1328]" captionStart="FIGURES 36–37" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[248,1336,200,1917]" captionTargetId="figure-23@18.[232,1356,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 36–37. Indoceoplanetes (Indoceoplanetes) fodincana new species ex Coracina papuensis oriomo. 36, male habitus, dorsal and ventral views. 37, female habitus, dorsal and ventral views." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825571" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825571/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Fig. 36</figureCitation>
; tergopleurite IV with 1 
<emphasis box="[1089,1111,1303,1328]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">ss</emphasis>
on each side, tergopleurite V with 2 
<emphasis box="[230,252,1339,1364]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">ss</emphasis>
on each side, tergopleurite VI with 3 
<emphasis box="[678,708,1339,1364]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">sts</emphasis>
on each side; sternite III with 2 
<emphasis box="[1073,1103,1339,1364]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">sts</emphasis>
on each side; abdominal segment V with 1 
<emphasis box="[313,338,1375,1400]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">ps</emphasis>
on each side. Basal apodeme rounded proximally, with concave lateral margins (
<figureCitation box="[1232,1315,1374,1400]" captionStart="FIGURES 38–42" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[186,1380,189,1897]" captionTargetId="figure-17@19.[186,1402,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 38–42. Indoceoplanetes (Indoceoplanetes) fodincana new species ex Coracina papuensis oriomo. 38, male head, dorsal and ventral views. 39, male genitalia, dorsal view. 40, male mesosome, ventral view. 41, male paramere, dorsal view. 42, female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825573" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825573/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Fig. 39</figureCitation>
). Proximal mesosome with broad antero-lateral extensions (
<figureCitation box="[693,776,1410,1436]" captionStart="FIGURES 38–42" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[186,1380,189,1897]" captionTargetId="figure-17@19.[186,1402,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 38–42. Indoceoplanetes (Indoceoplanetes) fodincana new species ex Coracina papuensis oriomo. 38, male head, dorsal and ventral views. 39, male genitalia, dorsal view. 40, male mesosome, ventral view. 41, male paramere, dorsal view. 42, female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825573" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825573/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Fig. 40</figureCitation>
), and anterior margin concave. Mesosomal lobes divergent distally. Distal margin of mesosome concave. Gonopore with antero-lateral extensions as in 
<figureCitation box="[1192,1275,1446,1472]" captionStart="FIGURES 38–42" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[186,1380,189,1897]" captionTargetId="figure-17@19.[186,1402,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 38–42. Indoceoplanetes (Indoceoplanetes) fodincana new species ex Coracina papuensis oriomo. 38, male head, dorsal and ventral views. 39, male genitalia, dorsal view. 40, male mesosome, ventral view. 41, male paramere, dorsal view. 42, female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825573" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825573/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Fig. 40</figureCitation>
. Dorsal fringe not tilted posteriorly and without thumb-like process. Chaetotaxy: 1 ventral 
<emphasis box="[1004,1076,1483,1508]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">gpmes</emphasis>
microseta on each side of distal gonopore; 2 
<emphasis box="[298,363,1518,1544]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">lpmes</emphasis>
sensilla on each mesosomal lobe, situated inside the rugose area and difficult to see in some specimens; 1 dorsal 
<emphasis box="[381,439,1555,1580]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">ames</emphasis>
microseta on each side distal to dorsal fringe. Parameres and 
<emphasis box="[1139,1214,1554,1580]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">pst1–2</emphasis>
as in 
<figureCitation box="[1282,1365,1554,1580]" captionStart="FIGURES 38–42" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[186,1380,189,1897]" captionTargetId="figure-17@19.[186,1402,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 38–42. Indoceoplanetes (Indoceoplanetes) fodincana new species ex Coracina papuensis oriomo. 38, male head, dorsal and ventral views. 39, male genitalia, dorsal view. 40, male mesosome, ventral view. 41, male paramere, dorsal view. 42, female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825573" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825573/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Fig. 41</figureCitation>
. Measurements as in 
<tableCitation box="[330,414,1590,1616]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="47.[151,239,457,483]" captionText="TABLE 1. Measurements (in mm) of species treated in this paper. Abbreviations used: TL = total length; HL = head length (along midline); HW = head width (at temples); PRW = prothorax width; PTW = pterothorax width; AW = abdominal width (at segment V). Note: many specimens had distorted abdomens, as noted below; consequently, the TL of many specimens could not be measured. Mean values are given in parentheses only where 10 or more individuals were measured. N = number of specimens examined." pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Table 1</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,762,1976]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,293,1626,1653]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Female.</emphasis>
Thoracic and abdominal chaetotaxy as in 
<figureCitation box="[772,855,1626,1652]" captionStart="FIGURES 36–37" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[248,1336,200,1917]" captionTargetId="figure-23@18.[232,1356,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 36–37. Indoceoplanetes (Indoceoplanetes) fodincana new species ex Coracina papuensis oriomo. 36, male habitus, dorsal and ventral views. 37, female habitus, dorsal and ventral views." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825571" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825571/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Fig. 37</figureCitation>
. Subgenital plate as in 
<figureCitation box="[1117,1200,1626,1652]" captionStart="FIGURES 38–42" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[186,1380,189,1897]" captionTargetId="figure-17@19.[186,1402,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 38–42. Indoceoplanetes (Indoceoplanetes) fodincana new species ex Coracina papuensis oriomo. 38, male head, dorsal and ventral views. 39, male genitalia, dorsal view. 40, male mesosome, ventral view. 41, male paramere, dorsal view. 42, female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825573" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825573/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Fig. 42</figureCitation>
, with lateral margins concave distally. Vulval margin gently rounded, with 2 short, slender 
<emphasis box="[956,1000,1663,1688]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">vms</emphasis>
and 1–2 short, thorn-like 
<emphasis box="[1303,1337,1663,1688]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">vss</emphasis>
on each side; 5–6 slender 
<emphasis box="[349,386,1699,1724]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">vos</emphasis>
on each side of subgenital plate; distal 2 
<emphasis box="[850,887,1699,1724]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">vos</emphasis>
median to 
<emphasis box="[1014,1048,1699,1724]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">vss</emphasis>
and substantially longer than 
<emphasis box="[1386,1430,1699,1724]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">vms</emphasis>
. Measurements as in 
<tableCitation box="[380,464,1734,1760]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="47.[151,239,457,483]" captionText="TABLE 1. Measurements (in mm) of species treated in this paper. Abbreviations used: TL = total length; HL = head length (along midline); HW = head width (at temples); PRW = prothorax width; PTW = pterothorax width; AW = abdominal width (at segment V). Note: many specimens had distorted abdomens, as noted below; consequently, the TL of many specimens could not be measured. Mean values are given in parentheses only where 10 or more individuals were measured. N = number of specimens examined." pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Table 1</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,762,1976]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1770,1796]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species epithet is derived from “ 
<emphasis box="[776,834,1770,1796]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">fodio</emphasis>
”, Latin for “dig or mine”, and “ 
<emphasis box="[1217,1304,1771,1796]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">incanus</emphasis>
”, Latin for “grey”, referring to the grey plumage of the host species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
