<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,150,465]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,367,393]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Remarks.</emphasis>
Most of the specimens from 
<emphasis box="[643,843,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">C. p. angustifrons</emphasis>
are poorly preserved, but tentatively identified as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gustafsson &amp; Bush" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Indoceoplanetes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psocodea" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fodincana" subGenus="Indoceoplanetes">
<emphasis box="[1406,1437,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">In.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[161,191,403,428]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">In.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[206,318,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">fodincana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on the characters that can be observed. More specimens are needed to confirm that the population living on this host subspecies is conspecific with those living on other host subspecies.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
